    "(15)According to Lemma 3,D(λ ⋆ p) -D p (λ ⋆ p) ≤ (M + β + M λ ⋆ p 1)ν.",
    "(16)After letting λ = λ ⋆ p in (15), we add up ( 15) and ( 16) from both sides to obtainD p (λ ⋆ p) ≥ D(λ ⋆) -(M + β + M λ ⋆ p 1)ν + µ ⋆ D 2 λ ⋆ p -λ ⋆ 2or, equivalently, λ ⋆ p -λ ⋆ 2 ≤ 2 µ ⋆ D D p (λ ⋆ p) -D(λ ⋆) + 2 µ ⋆ D (M + β + M λ ⋆ p 1)ν.",
    "(17) B.6 Proof of Concavity of Perturbation FunctionThe proof is an application of the duality between smoothness and strong convexity.",
    "With Assumption 6, P ⋆ (ϵ) is always finite for any ϵ ∈ E. It is also known that P ⋆ (ϵ) is upper semi-continuous for strictly feasible problems [4].",
    "To show that the perturbation function P ⋆ (ϵ) is strongly concave with parameter 1/L D over E, it is equivalent to show that P † (λ) is smooth with parameter L D. We note that P † (λ) = -D(λ) by the definition."
